Class GoogleTransport

HTTP transport for Google API's. It's only purpose is to allow for method overriding when the firewall does not accept DELETE, PATCH or PUT methods. Warning: scheduled in version 1.1 to no longer extend HttpTransport @since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class GoogleTransport, HttpTransport create()

Creates and returns a new HTTP transport with basic default behaviors for working with Google API's.

Includes:

  • Setting the HttpTransport.defaultHeaders to a new instance of GoogleHeaders.
  • Adding a MethodOverrideIntercepter as the first HTTP execute intercepter to use HTTP method override for unsupported HTTP methods (calls MethodOverrideIntercepter.setAsFirstFor(HttpTransport).

Sample usage: 

 
  static HttpTransport createTransport() {
    HttpTransport transport = GoogleHeadersGoogleTransport.create();
    GoogleHeaders headers = (GoogleHeaders) transport.defaultHeaders;
    headers.setApplicationName("acme-rocket-2");
    headers.gdataVersion = "2";
    return transport;
  }
@return HTTP transport
